cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CE 

This paper presents a new method for matrix and tensor factorization, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method is designed to handle integer data, which is often encountered in event counts or ordinal measures, making it relevant to data science (cs.DS). The paper also evaluates the method on Electronic Health Record (EHR) datasets, which involves working with large amounts of data and potentially using database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper applies the method to extract patient phenotypes, which is a topic in clinical informatics (cs.CE).
